<plot>One correction - this has nothing to do with break dancing or hip hop, look more at the Mod Allnighters of the 60's or the Nighters of such places as Wigan Casino, Twisted Wheel, Mecca etc... Or any of the Scooter Rallies to get a handle on the music.... Northern Soul - majority 60's, superior to Motown and Atlantic/Stax... Precursor of early 1970's disco (most folk know a lot of northern but class it as 70's disco) A taster selection - 1. Judy Street - What 2. Julain Covey - A little bit hurt 3. The Younghearts - A little togetherness 4. Edwin Starr - Agent 00 Soul 5. Al Wilson - One night affair Cheers Baggy ov the Upstarts Scooter Club Mansfield, Nott's......</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?206797</url></doc>
